Dear Sarah,

Thank you for our productive meeting earlier today. I am writing to formally confirm Baker & Associates LLP's engagement to represent Meridian Corporation in the contemplated patent infringement action against Pinnacle Industries, Inc. concerning U.S. Patent No. 9,876,543.

As discussed, our preliminary assessment indicates that Meridian has a strong case for patent infringement based on Pinnacle's AutoForge Multi-Stage Compression Platform, which appears to incorporate the thermal compression molding technology licensed to Pinnacle under the Technology License Agreement (TLA-2023-0032), but being used well outside the authorized Field of Use. The fact that Pinnacle had direct access to the Technical Package and subsequently developed a competing product creates a compelling narrative.

Our team for this matter will include myself as lead partner, Daniel Crawford as senior associate, and Michael Park as the associate handling day-to-day discovery matters. We will also be engaging Amanda Foster, our senior paralegal specializing in patent litigation, to manage the document review process. I anticipate we will need to retain technical and damages experts within the first 60 days of filing; I will provide recommendations for your consideration shortly.

Our engagement letter, including fee arrangements and billing procedures, is attached for your review and signature. Please note that our standard billing rates will apply, with partner time at $850/hour, senior associate time at $575/hour, associate time at $425/hour, and paralegal time at $275/hour. We estimate initial costs through filing and the case management conference at approximately $75,000-$100,000.

I recommend we target filing the complaint within the next three to four weeks, after we complete our pre-filing investigation and finalize the complaint. I will circulate a draft complaint for your review by September 1. In the meantime, please ensure that Meridian preserves all documents and communications related to the Pinnacle relationship, the '543 Patent, and the AutoForge System, and issue a litigation hold notice to all relevant custodians.

Please do not hesitate to call me if you have any questions. I look forward to working with you and the Meridian team on this important matter.

